history.content:
<md>I took 61BL. I personally enjoyed it because more of the learning was in the work instead of just in lecture. In terms of difficulty, it depends on the projects they chose for the semester but I would not say it's too bad. 
If you are confident in your ability with the class content due to prior knowledge, it probably would be fine adding another summer class for the summer but I found it to be enough work to keep me busy for most of the time.</md>

How hard is CS 61BL? I plan on taking it in the summer of this year so I can declare EECS. Furthermore, I am wondering if it would be a great idea to add another summer class to my load this summer.
Thank You,
Ryota Inagaki
history.subject: Insights into CS 61BL
